
/*
 * // This Hyperlambda code retrieves the value of a node named "message" that is a child of the ".arguments" node. The [get-value] slot is used to access the value of the specified node, which is useful for extracting specific data from a structured node hierarchy.
 * // 1. [get-value] - Retrieves the value of the node specified by the expression.
 * // 2. [x:@.arguments/*/message] - Expression pointing to the "message" node under ".arguments".
 */
get-value:x:@.arguments/*/message
